(15, '<div class=\"SPZz6b\" role=\"heading\" aria-level=\"3\">\r\n<h1 class=\"kno-ecr-pt kno-fb-ctx gsmt\" style=\"text-align: center;\" data-local-attribute=\"d3bn\" data-ved=\"2ahUKEwiIsKTL8fbfAhUjQxUIHRTMBkQQ3B0oATAnegQIBRAd\"><strong>Solar System</strong></h1>\r\n<div class=\"wwUB2c kno-fb-ctx\"><span data-ved=\"2ahUKEwiIsKTL8fbfAhUjQxUIHRTMBkQQ2kooAjAnegQIBRAe\">Star system</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"mod\" lang=\"en-CM\" style=\"clear: none;\" data-md=\"50\" data-hveid=\"CAkQAA\" data-ved=\"2ahUKEwiIsKTL8fbfAhUjQxUIHRTMBkQQkCkwKHoECAkQAA\">\r\n<div class=\"hb8SAc kno-fb-ctx\" data-hveid=\"CAkQAQ\" data-ved=\"2ahUKEwiIsKTL8fbfAhUjQxUIHRTMBkQQziAoADAoegQICRAB\">\r\n<div class=\"r-iigroDXHsVXs\">\r\n<div class=\"kno-rdesc r-iCGUE9TTsOSI\" data-rtid=\"iCGUE9TTsOSI\">\r\n<div>\r\n<h3 class=\"bNg8Rb\">Description</h3>\r\nThe Solar System is the gravitationally bound system of the Sun and the objects that orbit it, either directly or indirectly. Of the objects that orbit the Sun directly, the largest are the eight planets, with the remainder being smaller objects, such as the five dwarf planets and small Solar System bodies. <a class=\"q ruhjFe NJLBac fl\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solar_System\" data-ved=\"2ahUKEwiIsKTL8fbfAhUjQxUIHRTMBkQQmhMwKHoECAkQAg\">Wikipedia</a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"mod\" lang=\"en-CM\" style=\"clear: none;\" data-attrid=\"ss:/webfacts:known_planet\" data-md=\"1001\" data-hveid=\"CAkQBA\" data-ved=\"2ahUKEwiIsKTL8fbfAhUjQxUIHRTMBkQQkCkwKnoECAkQBA\">\r\n<div class=\"Z1hOCe\">\r\n<div class=\"zloOqf kno-fb-ctx\" data-ved=\"2ahUKEwiIsKTL8fbfAhUjQxUIHRTMBkQQyxMoADAqegQICRAF\"><span class=\"w8qArf\"><a class=\"fl\" href=\"https://www.google.com/search?client=firefox-b-ab&amp;q=solar+system+known+planets&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=2ahUKEwiIsKTL8fbfAhUjQxUIHRTMBkQQ6BMoADAqegQICRAG\" data-ved=\"2ahUKEwiIsKTL8fbfAhUjQxUIHRTMBkQQ6BMoADAqegQICRAG\">Known planets</a>: </span><span class=\"LrzXr kno-fv\