(29, '<p>#BIBLE VERSE DESKTOP&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>#name&nbsp; &nbsp; New King James Version</p>\r\n<p>#abbr&nbsp; &nbsp; NKJV</p>\r\n<p>#language english</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>; Scripture taken from the New King James Version.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>; Сopyright &copy; 1979, 1980, 1982 by Thomas Nelson, Inc.</p>\r\n<p>; Used by permission. All rights reserved.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>And God saw the light, that it was good; and God divided the light from the darkness. Gen.1:4</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Do not be afraid. Stand still, and see the salvation of the LORD Ex.14:13</p>\r\n<p>I will make all My goodness pass before you Ex.33:19</p>\r\n<p>The LORD God, merciful and gracious Ex.34:6</p>\r\n<p>I will set My tabernacle among you Lev.26:11</p>\r\n<p>I will walk among you and be your God Lev.26:12</p>\r\n<p>The LORD is longsuffering and abundant in mercy Num.14:18</p>\r\n<p>You shall love the LORD your God with all your heart Deut.6:5</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Only be strong and very courageous Josh.1:7</p>\r\n<p>This Book of the Law shall not depart from your mouth Josh.1:8</p>\r\n<p>Have I not commanded you? Be strong and of good courage Josh.1:9</p>\r\n<p>Do not be afraid, nor be dismayed, for the LORD your God is with you Josh.1:9</p>\r\n<p>Sanctify yourselves, for tomorrow the LORD will do wonders among you Josh.3:5</p>\r\n<p>The LORD your God is He who fights for you Josh.23:10</p>\r\n<p>No, but we will serve the LORD! Josh.24:21</p>\r\n<p>I will never break My covenant with you Judg.2:1</p>\r\n<p>Those who love Him be like the sun when it comes out in full strength Judg.5:31</p>\r\n<p>Your people shall be my people, and your God, my God Ruth 1:16</p>\r\n<p>He will guard the feet of His saints 1Sam.2:9</p>\r\n<p>Only fear the LORD, and serve Him in truth with all your heart 1Sam.12:24</p>\r\n<p>I will show you what you shall do 1Sam.16:3</p>\r\n<p>Man looks at the outward appearance, but the LORD looks at the heart 1Sam.16:7</p>\r\n<p>He has made with me an everlasting covenant 2Sam.23:5</p>\r\n<p>Give to Your servant an understanding heart 1Kin.3:9</p>\r\n<p>The LORD your God you shall fear; and He will deliver you 2Kin.17:39</p>\r\n<p>Serve Him with a loyal heart and with a willing mind 1Chr.28:9</p>\r\n<p>The LORD searches all hearts and understands all the intent of the thoughts 1Chr.28:9</p>\r\n<p>If you seek Him, He will be found by you 1Chr.28:9</p>\r\n<p>The LORD is able to give you much more than this 2Chr.25:9</p>\r\n<p>Will not turn His face from you if you return to Him 2Chr.30:9</p>\r\n<p>He did it with all his heart. So he prospered 2Chr.31:21</p>\r\n<p>The hand of our God is upon all those for good who seek Him Ezdra 8:22</p>\r\n<p>The joy of the LORD is your strength Neh.8:10</p>\r\n<p>Yet who knows whether you have come to the kingdom for such a time as this? Esther.4:14</p>\r\n<p>He will yet fill your mouth with laughing, and your lips with rejoicing Job 8:21</p>\r\n<p>I know that my Redeemer lives Job 19:25</p>\r\n<p>Blessed is the man who walks not in the counsel of the ungodly Ps.1:1</p>\r\n<p>The LORD knows the way of the righteous Ps.1:6</p>\r\n<p>Serve the LORD with fear, and rejoice with trembling Ps.2:11</p>\r\n<p>Blessed are all those who put their trust in Him Ps.2:12</p>\r\n<p>But You, O LORD, are a shield for me, my glory Ps.3:3</p>\r\n<p>Lead me, O LORD, in Your righteousness Ps.5:8</p>\r\n<p>For You, O LORD, will bless the righteous Ps.5:12</p>\r\n<p>For the righteous God tests the hearts and minds Ps.7:9</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For You, LORD, have not forsaken those who seek You Ps.9:10</p>\r\n<p>The LORD is King forever and ever Ps.10:16</p>\r\n<p>LORD, You have heard the desire of the humble Ps.10:17</p>\r\n<p>O LORD, You are the portion of my inheritance and my cup Ps.16:5</p>\r\n<p>Hide me under the shadow of Your wings Ps.17:8</p>\r\n<p>I will love You, O LORD, my strength Ps.18:1</p>\r\n<p>The LORD is my rock and my fortress and my deliverer Ps.18:2</p>\r\n<p>For You will light my lamp Ps.18:28</p>\r\n<p>The LORD my God will enlighten my darkness Ps.18:28</p>\r\n<p>It is God who arms me with strength Ps.18:32</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Let the God of my salvation be exalted Ps.18:46</p>\r\n<p>The heavens declare the glory of God; and the firmament shows His handiwork Ps.19:1</p>\r\n<p>The law of the LORD is perfect, converting the soul Ps.19:7</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The fear of the LORD is clean, enduring forever Ps.19:9</p>\r\n<p>The judgments of the LORD are true and righteous altogether Ps.19:9</p>\r\n<p>Some trust in chariots, and some in horses; but we will remember the name of the LORD our God. Ps.20:7</p>\r\n<p>Those who seek Him will praise the LORD Ps.22:26</p>\r\n<p>All the ends of the world shall remember and turn to the LORD Ps.22:27</p>\r\n<p>A posterity shall serve Him Ps.22:30</p>\r\n<p>The LORD is my shepherd; I shall not want Ps.23:1</p>\r\n<p>The LORD strong and mighty, the LORD mighty in battle Ps.24:8</p>\r\n<p>O my God, I trust in You; let me not be ashamed Ps.25:2</p>\r\n<p>Show me Your ways, O LORD; teach me Your paths. Ps.25:4</p>\r\n<p>Good and upright is the LORD; therefore He teaches sinners in the way Ps.25:8</p>\r\n<p>The secret of the LORD is with those who fear Him Ps.25:14</p>\r\n<p>My eyes are ever toward the LORD, for He shall pluck my feet out of the net. Ps.25:15</p>\r\n<p>Teach me Your way, O LORD Ps.27:11</p>\r\n<p>Wait on the LORD; be of good courage, and He shall strengthen your heart Ps.27:14</p>\r\n<p>The LORD is my strength and my shield Ps.28:7</p>\r\n<p>My heart trusted in Him, and I am helped Ps.28:7</p>\r\n<p>The voice of the LORD is powerful; the voice of the LORD is full of majesty Ps.29:4</p>\r\n<p>The LORD will give strength to His people Ps.29:11</p>\r\n<p>The LORD will bless His people with peace Ps.29:11</p>\r\n<p>His favor is for life Ps.30:5</p>\r\n<p>Be of good courage, and He shall strengthen your heart Ps.31:24</p>\r\n<p>Blessed is he whose transgression is forgiven Ps.32:1</p>\r\n<p>I will instruct you and teach you in the way you should go Ps.32:8</p>\r\n<p>He who trusts in the LORD, mercy shall surround him Ps.32:10</p>\r\n<p>Be glad in the LORD and rejoice! Ps.32:11</p>\r\n<p>For the word of the LORD is right, and all His work is done in truth Ps.33:4</p>\r\n<p>The earth is full of the goodness of the LORD Ps.33:5</p>\r\n<p>Our soul waits for the LORD; He is our help and our shield. Ps.33:20</p>\r\n<p>They looked to Him and were radiant Ps.34:5</p>\r\n<p>Oh, taste and see that the LORD is good Ps.34:8</p>\r\n<p>Those who seek the LORD shall not lack any good thing Ps.34:10</p>\r\n<p>The LORD is near to those who have a broken heart Ps.34:18</p>\r\n<p>And my soul shall be joyful in the LORD; it shall rejoice in His salvation. Ps.35:9</p>\r\n<p>Trust in the LORD, and do good Ps.37:3</p>\r\n<p>Dwell in the land, and feed on His faithfulness Ps.37:3</p>\r\n<p>Delight yourself also in the LORD, and He shall give you the desires of your heart Ps.37:4</p>\r\n<p>Commit your way to the LORD, trust also in Him, and He shall bring it to pass. Ps.37:5</p>\r\n<p>Rest in the LORD, and wait patiently for Him Ps.37:7</p>\r\n<p>The meek shall inherit the earth, and shall delight themselves in the abundance of peace Ps.37:11</p>\r\n<p>Wait on the LORD, and keep His way Ps.37:34</p>\r\n<p>The salvation of the righteous is from the LORD; He is their strength in the time of trouble. Ps.37:39</p>\r\n<p>Lord, all my desire is before You Ps.38:9</p>\r\n<p>Blessed is that man who makes the LORD his trust Ps.40:4</p>\r\n<p>I delight to do Your will, O my God Ps.40:8</p>\r\n<p>Be still, and know that I am God Ps.46:10</p>\r\n<p>Oh, clap your hands, all you peoples! Shout to God with the voice of triumph! Ps.47:1</p>\r\n<p>The redemption of their souls is costly Ps.49:9</p>\r\n<p>Our God shall come, and shall not keep silent Ps.50:3</p>\r\n<p>Offer to God thanksgiving, and pay your vows to the Most High Ps.50:14</p>\r\n<p>Call upon Me in the day of trouble; I will deliver you Ps.50:15</p>\r\n<p>Whoever offers praise glorifies Me Ps.50:23</p>\r\n<p>The fool has said in his heart, \"There is no God\" Ps.53:1</p>\r\n<p>Behold, God is my helper; the Lord is with those who uphold my life Ps.54:4</p>\r\n<p>Cast your burden on the LORD, and He shall sustain you Ps.55:22</p>\r\n<p>He shall never permit the righteous to be moved Ps.55:22</p>\r\n<p>Surely there is a reward for the righteous Ps.58:11</p>\r\n<p>God is my defense, my God of mercy Ps.59:17</p>\r\n<p>Truly my soul silently waits for God; from Him comes my salvation Ps.62:1</p>\r\n<p>God is a refuge for us Ps.62:8</p>\r\n<p>God has spoken once, twice I have heard this: that power belongs to God. Ps.62:11</p>\r\n<p>The righteous shall be glad in the LORD, and trust in Him Ps.64:10</p>\r\n<p>Your God has commanded your strength Ps.68:28</p>\r\n<p>But it is good for me to draw near to God Ps.73:28</p>\r\n<p>Open your mouth wide, and I will fill it Ps.81:10</p>\r\n<p>The LORD God is a sun and shield Ps.84:11</p>\r\n<p>The LORD will give grace and glory Ps.84:11</p>\r\n<p>The LORD will give what is good; and our land will yield its increase. Ps.85:12</p>\r\n<p>For You, Lord, are good, and ready to forgive, and abundant in mercy Ps.86:5</p>\r\n<p>He who dwells in the secret place of the Most High Shall abide under the shadow of the Almighty Ps.91:1</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Lest you dash your foot against a stone Ps.91:12</p>\r\n<p>The righteous shall flourish like a palm tree Ps.92:12</p>\r\n<p>The LORD reigns, He is clothed with majesty Ps.93:1</p>\r\n<p>The LORD knows the thoughts of man, that they are futile Ps.94:11</p>\r\n<p>The LORD will not cast off His people Ps.94:14</p>\r\n<p>Give to the LORD the glory due His name Ps.96:8</p>\r\n<p>Worship the LORD in the beauty of holiness! Ps.96:9</p>\r\n<p>The LORD reigns; the world also is firmly established, it shall not be moved Ps.96:10</p>\r\n<p>Light is sown for the righteous, and gladness for the upright in heart Ps.97:11</p>\r\n<p>The LORD has made known His salvation Ps.98:2</p>\r\n<p>Serve the LORD with gladness Ps.100:2</p>\r\n<p>I will set nothing wicked before my eyes Ps.101:3</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Bless the LORD, O my soul, and forget not all His benefits Ps.103:2</p>\r\n<p>Forget not all His benefits Ps.103:2</p>\r\n<p>Who forgives all your iniquities, who heals all your diseases Ps.103:3</p>\r\n<p>As the heavens are high above the earth, so great is His mercy Ps.103:11</p>\r\n<p>As far as the east is from the west, so far has He removed our transgressions from us Ps.103:12</p>\r\n<p>I will sing to the LORD as long as I live Ps.104:33</p>\r\n<p>Let the hearts of those rejoice who seek the LORD! Ps.105:3</p>\r\n<p>Seek the LORD and His strength; seek His face evermore! Ps.105:4</p>\r\n<p>O give thanks to the LORD, for He is good! For His mercy endures forever. Ps.106:1</p>\r\n<p>He sent His word and healed them Ps.107:20</p>\r\n<p>Through God we will do valiantly Ps.108:13</p>\r\n<p>I will greatly praise the LORD with my mouth Ps.109:30</p>\r\n<p>He raises the poor out of the dust, and lifts the needy out of the ash heap Ps.113:7</p>\r\n<p>You who fear the LORD, trust in the LORD; He is their help and their shield Ps.115:11</p>\r\n<p>He will bless those who fear the LORD Ps.115:13</p>\r\n<p>I will take up the cup of salvation, and call upon the name of the LORD Ps.116:13</p>\r\n<p>His merciful kindness is great toward us Ps.117:2</p>\r\n<p>It is better to trust in the LORD than to put confidence in man Ps.118:8</p>\r\n<p>The LORD is my strength and song, and He has become my salvation Ps.118:14</p>\r\n<p>The right hand of the LORD does valiantly Ps.118:16</p>\r\n<p>This is the day the LORD has made; we will rejoice and be glad in it Ps.118:24</p>\r\n<p>Yo